{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Cslib/Foundations/Combinatorics/InfiniteGraphRamsey.html#Cslib.infinite_graph_ramsey\"><span class=\"name\">Cslib</span>.<span class=\"name\">infinite_graph_ramsey</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Vertex</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Color</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finite/Defs.html#Finite\">Finite</a> <span class=\"fn\">Color</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">color</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">Vertex</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\">Color</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finite/Defs.html#Infinite\">Infinite</a> <span class=\"fn\">Vertex</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <span class=\"fn\">Color</span>) (<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">Vertex</span></span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">s</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finite/Defs.html#Set.Infinite\">Infinite</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">Vertex</span></span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">e</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Card.html#Finset.card\">card</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">e</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#HasSubset.Subset\">⊆</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">color</span> <span class=\"fn\">e</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If the edges of an infinite complete graph is assigned a finite number of colors,\nthen there must exist a color `c` and an infinite set `s` of vertices such that the edge\nbeteen any two vertices of `s` is assigned the same color `c`. ","docLink":"./Cslib/Foundations/Combinatorics/InfiniteGraphRamsey.html#Cslib.infinite_graph_ramsey","kind":"theorem","line":122,"name":"Cslib.infinite_graph_ramsey","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/b00648a4fe741981bb586a3cc845258ab1583f61/Cslib/Foundations/Combinatorics/InfiniteGraphRamsey.lean#L122-L147"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Cslib/Foundations/Combinatorics/InfiniteGraphRamsey.html#Cslib.infinite_pigeonhole_principle\"><span class=\"name\">Cslib</span>.<span class=\"name\">infinite_pigeonhole_principle</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Y</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finite/Defs.html#Finite\">Finite</a> <span class=\"fn\">Y</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">X</span> → <span class=\"fn\">Y</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h_inf</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">s</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finite/Defs.html#Set.Infinite\">Infinite</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">y</span> : <span class=\"fn\">Y</span>) (<span class=\"fn\">t</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">t</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finite/Defs.html#Set.Infinite\">Infinite</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">t</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#HasSubset.Subset\">⊆</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">∀ <span class=\"fn\">x</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">t</span>, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">y</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"An infinite pigeonhole principle. ","docLink":"./Cslib/Foundations/Combinatorics/InfiniteGraphRamsey.html#Cslib.infinite_pigeonhole_principle","kind":"theorem","line":28,"name":"Cslib.infinite_pigeonhole_principle","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/b00648a4fe741981bb586a3cc845258ab1583f61/Cslib/Foundations/Combinatorics/InfiniteGraphRamsey.lean#L28-L38"}}],"imports":["Init","C